, this erudite but accessible book will be essential to anyone tackling the question of what it means to undertake critical and conceptually challenging fieldwork. Apprenticeship in Critical Ethnographic Practice explains how to seriously explore what it means to be human in a complex world—and why it is so important.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEthnologyzLiberia. 0aGola (African people)xSocial life and customs. 0aTailorszLiberiaxApprentices. 0aVai (African people)xSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aapprenticeship, vai, gola, tailors, liberia, fieldwork, anthropology, sociology, labor, africa, ethnology, nonfiction, academia, institutional arrangements, training, methodology, research, scholarship, learning transfer, development, education, skill building, monrovia, happy corner, artisan, activity, praxis, theory, communities of practice.1 aGibson, Thomas P.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022647071940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226470733423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226470733/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles